Wales Beats Argentina 28-13 in Final Rugby World Cup Warm-Up

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-20T15:32:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-20/wales-beats-argentina-28-13-in-final-rugby-world-cup-warm-up.html
Wales  defeated Argentina 28-13 in
the final warm-up match for both teams before the Rugby World
Cup.  Andy Powell, Alun-Wyn Jones and George North touched down
as Wales outscored Argentina three tries to one at the
Millennium Stadium in Cardiff, while James Hook kicked 13
points. Martin Scelzo touched down for Argentina, with Felipe
Contepomi kicking eight points.  Argentina opens play at the World Cup in New Zealand
against England on Sept. 10, while Wales plays its first game
the next day against defending champion  South Africa .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  